In a large saucepan, bring water and milk to a boil. Add grits, cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes or thickened. In a small bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir a small amount of hot grits into yolks; mix well. Return all to the pan, stirring constantly. Add 3/4 cup cheese, butter, chilies and salt. Pour into a greased 1-1/2-qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown.